title: Breathe In, Breathe Out, Move On
text:
 Tweet Share on Twitter  Share Share on Facebook  Pin Pinterest 1 Comment 
Hopefully we've gotten our NSFW Bleeding over and done with and I suggest that we all just Breathe In, Breathe Out, Move On. Hastily paraphrased in a bourbon and beer flooded mind, but I think this describes me best this morning. Sorry to the troubadour of beach music...I am a shameless thief. 
Breathe In Breathe Out Move On (will not let me embed apologies but I suggest you click and sing along) I bought a cheap seat from a drunken fan Strolling down Sanford It wasn’t on the 50 or near the band 
But it got me in the crowd Now you may be thinking that I was had But this ticket was the best in the land And on the back were the scribbled words Breathe In, Breathe Out, Move On And it rained, It was nothing really new And it blew, we've seen all that before And it poured, the stadium began to strain North Oconee leaking through the floor, The Tide was at the door Now a humbled loss doesn't leave you dead It just makes you strong Don't try to explain it just nod your head Breathe In, Breathe Out, Move On And it rained, It was nothing really new And it blew, we've seen all that before And it poured, the stadium began to strain The Oconee River flooded Tate Building to the 2nd floor According to that scribble on my ticket it is just now Past is dead and gone Don't try to shake it just nod your head Breathe In, Breathe Out, Move On Don't try to shake it just bow your head
